  "text": "where s ∈ R is a natural estimate for dim B F ∅ , such as similarity dimension in the self-similar case [CITATION_1] or upper Lipschitz dimension [CITATION_2] in the general case. This exploits the abundance of literature on the equality of s and dim B F ∅ in different settings, which may then determine precise conditions for equality. In the affine setting, the natural candidate for s is the affinity dimension, and we prove (1.2) holds in this case.",
